Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.30,0:04:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,在這艘想像之舟中\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}In this ship of the Imagination,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.30,0:04:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,不受空間和時間的限制\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}free from the shackles of space and time,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.94,0:04:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,我們可以去任何地方\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}we can go anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.01,0:04:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你想知道我們身處太空何處\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}If you want to see where we are in space,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.28,0:04:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,只要看向窗外\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}just look out the front window.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.38,0:04:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,以時間來說 過去就在我們腳下\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}In the dimension of time, the past lies beneath us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.32,0:04:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是地球2.5億年前的樣子\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Here's what Earth looked like 250 million years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.13,0:04:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,抬頭 就可以看到未來的樣子\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}If you want to see the future, look up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.73,0:04:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是2.5億年後可能的樣子\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}And this is how it could appear 250 million years from now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.37,0:04:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我們要嘗試\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}If we're going to be venturing out
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.84,0:04:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,在極度廣闊的宇宙中聯繫\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}into the farthest reaches of the cosmos,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.71,0:04:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,我們需要知道自己的宇宙地址\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}we need to know our cosmic address,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.65,0:04:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是我們地址的第一行\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}and this is the first line of that address.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.35,0:04:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,地球
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.06,0:05:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,我們現在離開地球 這個我們僅有的家園\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}We're leaving the Earth, the only home we've ever known,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.46,0:05:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,向更加寬廣的宇宙進發\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}for the farthest reaches of the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.24,0:05:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我們最近的鄰居 月球 沒有大氣層\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Our nearest neighbor, the Moon, has no sky,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.15,0:05:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有海洋 沒有生命\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}no ocean, no life...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.58,0:05:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,只有天體撞擊的傷痕\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}just the scars of cosmic impacts.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.97,0:05:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的地球為我們提供了風和浪\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Our star powers the wind and the waves
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.97,0:05:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,為地球表面一切的生物提供能量\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}and all the life on the surface of our world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.81,0:06:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,從水星開始\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}The Sun holds all the worlds of the solar system
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.41,0:06:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,整個太陽系都被太陽的引力場所包圍\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}in its gravitational embrace, starting with Mercury...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.50,0:06:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,直到雲層覆蓋的金星\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}...to cloud-covered Venus, where runaway greenhouse effect
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.44,0:06:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,失控的溫室效應把它變成一座煉獄\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}has turned it into a kind of hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.98,0:06:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,火星\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Mars...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.82,0:06:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,表面積和地球相近\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}a world with as much land as Earth itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.00,0:07:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,一條岩石似的小行星帶\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}A belt of rocky asteroids circles the Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.34,0:07:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,在火星和木星的軌道間圍繞太陽運行\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}between the orbits of Mars and Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.32,0:07:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,木星被四個大衛星和幾十個小衛星環繞\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}With its four giant moons and dozens of smaller ones,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.65,0:07:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,木星好像擁有自己的太陽系一般\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Jupiter is like its own little solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.16,0:07:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,它的質量超過所有其他行星的總和\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}It has more mass than all the other planets combined.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.21,0:07:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,木星的大紅斑\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Jupiter's Great Red Spot...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.21,0:07:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,它是一個比地球大3倍的古老風暴\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}a hurricane three times the size of our whole planet
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.38,0:07:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,已經存在了幾百年之久\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}that's been raging for centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.37,0:08:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,土星宛如太陽系中皇冠上的明珠\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}The crown jewel of our solar system, Saturn,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.27,0:08:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,被無數運行軌道和緩慢翻滾的雪球所環繞\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}ringed by freeways of countless orbiting and slowly tumbling snowballs...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.95,0:08:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,每個雪球的體積相當於一個小月亮\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}every snowball, a little moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.28,0:08:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,天王星\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Uranus...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.48,0:08:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,還有海王星\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}and Neptune,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.49,0:09:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,這顆古人未知的最偏遠的行星\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}the outermost planets, unknown to the ancients
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.82,0:09:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,直到望遠鏡發明後才被發現\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}and only discovered after the invention of the telescope.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.00,0:09:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,在這最偏遠的行星之外\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Beyond the outermost planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.40,0:09:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,還有成千上萬的冰凍世界\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}there's a swarm of tens of thousands of frozen worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.59,0:09:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,冥王星就是其中一個\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}And Pluto is one them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.90,0:09:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,在我們所有的航天器中\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Of all our spacecraft,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.34,0:09:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,這是離家最遠的一個\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}this is the one that's traveled farthest from home...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.68,0:09:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,旅行者1號\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Voyager 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.68,0:09:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs18\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI}於1977年9月5日發射 截止到2012年6月仍然正常運作\n它是有史以來距離地球最遠的人造飛行器
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.91,0:10:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,她承載著我們發向未來的信息\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}She bears a message to a billion years from now,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.91,0:10:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs18\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI}歷經36年的旅行 離地球約187億公里 是第一個離開太陽系的人造飛行器
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.58,0:10:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,關於我們是誰\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}something of who we were,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.58,0:10:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs18\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI}旅行者1號上攜帶了一張銅質磁盤唱片 內容包括用55種人類語言錄製的問候語和各類音樂\n旨在向「外星人」表達人類的問候
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.35,0:10:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的體會\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}how we felt
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.49,0:10:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs18\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI}55種人類語言中包括了四種中國的語言:粵語 國語 閩南語 吳語\n問候語為：「行星地球的孩子（向你們）問好」
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.52,0:10:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,以及我們創作的音樂\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}and the music we made.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.74,0:10:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,浩瀚宇宙海洋中\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}The deeper waters
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.60,0:10:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,更深層的水流裏\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}of this vast cosmic ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.47,0:10:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,也存在著數不盡的世界\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}and their numberless worlds lie ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.89,0:10:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,從這裏看 太陽好像和其他星星並無兩樣\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}From out here, the Sun may look like just another star.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.79,0:10:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,但它的引力場依然影響著\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}But it still exerts its gravitational hold
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.23,0:10:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,數萬億的冰凍彗星\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}on a trillion frozen comets,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.63,0:10:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,還有太陽系中那些形成於大約50億年前的\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}leftovers from the formation of the solar system
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.40,0:10:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,其他所有組成部分\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}nearly five billion years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.23,0:10:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,我們稱之為 奧爾特雲\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}It's called the Oort Cloud.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.87,0:11:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,以前從沒有人見過 也不可能見過\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}No one has ever seen it before, nor could they,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.61,0:11:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,因為這些天體\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}because each one of these little worlds
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.88,0:11:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,與它最近的鄰居之間的距離\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}is as far from its nearest neighbor
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.11,0:11:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,和地球與土星的距離差不多 (12-16億公里）\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}as Earth is from Saturn.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.75,0:11:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,這個包含太陽系的巨大彗星雲團\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}This enormous cloud of comets encloses the solar system,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.58,0:11:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,就是我們宇宙地址的第二行\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}which is the second line of our cosmic address.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.39,0:11:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,地球\n太陽系
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.29,0:11:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,我們有能力探測其他星系的行星\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}We've only been able to detect the planets of other stars
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.96,0:11:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,也就是最近幾十年的事情\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}for a few decades,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.97,0:11:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,但是我們已經知道行星的數量是很多的\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}but we already know that planets are plentiful...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.74,0:11:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,比恆星的數量要多得多\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}they outnumber the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.41,0:11:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,幾乎所有的行星都和地球很不一樣\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Almost all of them will be very different from Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.84,0:11:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,不適合生物生存\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}and hostile to life as we know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.34,0:11:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,但是我們對於生物又有多少瞭解呢？\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}But what do we know about life?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.75,0:11:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,目前我們只接觸過一種\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}We've met only one kind so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.82,0:11:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,地球生物\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Earthlife.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.79,0:11:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,看到什麼了嗎？\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}See anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.12,0:11:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,只是空蕩蕩的太空 對嗎\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Just empty space, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.12,0:11:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,人類的眼睛只能看到宇宙中的一絲光亮\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Human eyes see only a sliver of the light that shines in the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.93,0:11:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,但是科技讓我們可以看到肉眼無法看到的\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}But science gives us the power to see what our senses cannot.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.16,0:12:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,夜視鏡可以讓我們看見紅外線\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Infrared is the kind of light made visible by night-vision goggles.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.97,0:12:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,向黑暗中發射一個紅外感應器\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Throw an infrared sensor across the darkness...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.04,0:12:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,流浪行星\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Rogue planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.68,0:12:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,不繞恆星公轉的行星\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}World without a sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.85,0:12:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的銀河中有數十億顆遊蕩在永恆的黑夜中\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Our galaxy has billions of them, adrift in perpetual night.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.32,0:12:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,在他們原本的星系誕生時的混亂中\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}They're orphans, cast away from their mother stars
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.89,0:12:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,他們像孤兒一樣失去了恆星母親\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}during the chaotic birth of their native star systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.06,0:12:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,流浪行星有著熔岩般的內核\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Rogue planets are molten at the core
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.73,0:12:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,但表面卻被嚴寒覆蓋\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}but frozen at the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.73,0:12:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,在這些極端區域的中間\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}There may be oceans of liquid water
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.73,0:12:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,也許存在著大洋般的液態水\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}in the zone between those extremes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.31,0:12:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,誰又能知道水中生活著什麼東西呢\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Who knows what might be swimming there?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.68,0:12:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,這是銀河的紅外線顯示圖\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}This is what the Milky Way looks like in infrared.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.89,0:12:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,每個小點 不僅僅是那些明亮的\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Every single dot, not just the bright ones,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.99,0:12:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,都是一顆恆星\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}is a star.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.19,0:13:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,這裏有多少顆恆星\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}How many stars?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.19,0:13:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,有多少不同的世界呢\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}How many worlds?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.19,0:13:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,又有多少不同的生命存在的方式\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}How many ways of being alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.70,0:13:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我們又身處圖片中的何處呢\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Where are we in this picture?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.70,0:13:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,看到那條螺旋臂了嗎\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}See that trailing outer arm?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.70,0:13:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs18\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI}地球\n太陽系\n銀河系
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.17,0:13:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,我們就在那裏\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}That's where we live...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.37,0:13:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,距離中心3萬光年\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}about 30,000 light-years from the center.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.61,0:13:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,銀河系\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}The Milky Way Galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.34,0:13:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,我們宇宙地址的下一行\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}is the next line of our cosmic address.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.68,0:13:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,我們現在離家十萬光年\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}We're now a hundred thousand light-years from home.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.08,0:13:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,光波 存在的速度最快的東西\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}It would take light, the fastest thing there is,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.35,0:13:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,要花10萬年才能從地球到達我們這裏\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}a hundred thousand years to reach us from Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.96,0:13:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,這是僊女座螺旋星系\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}This is the Great Spiral in Andromeda,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.39,0:13:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,銀河系的隔壁鄰居\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}the galaxy next door.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.40,0:13:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,我們將這兩大星系\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}We call our two giant galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.40,0:13:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,和一些較小的星系稱為\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}and a smattering of smaller ones
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.40,0:13:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,本星系群\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}the "local group."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.83,0:13:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs18\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI}地球\n太陽系\n銀河系\n本星系群
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.12,0:13:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs18\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI}地球\n太陽系\n銀河系\n本星系群\n室女座超星系團
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.41,0:13:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,從這裏已經看不到銀河系了\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Can't even find our home galaxy from out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.75,0:13:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,它只是室女座超星系團中的幾千份之一\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}It's just one of thousands in the Virgo Supercluster.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.98,0:14:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,以這個比例來說\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}On this scale,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.92,0:14:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,我們所看到的 哪怕是最小的點\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}all the objects we see, including the tiniest dots,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.56,0:14:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,都是一個星系\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}are galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.39,0:14:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,每個星系包含幾十億顆恆星\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Each galaxy contains billions of suns
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.96,0:14:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,和數不清的行星世界\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}and countless worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.06,0:14:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,然而 整個室女座超星系團\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Yet, the entire Virgo Supercluster itself
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.73,0:14:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,只是我們宇宙的一個極小組成部分\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}forms but a tiny part of our universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.64,0:14:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,這是我們已知的最大範圍的宇宙\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}This is the cosmos on the grandest scale we know...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.64,0:14:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,一張由數以千億的星系組成的大網\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}a network of a hundred billion galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.98,0:14:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,也是我們宇宙地址的最後一行\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}It's the last line of our cosmic address...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.45,0:14:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,截止目前\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.98,0:14:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs18\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI}地球\n太陽系\n銀河系\n本星系群 室女座超星系團\n可觀測宇宙
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.02,0:14:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,可觀測宇宙\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Observable universe?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.52,0:14:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,什麼意思\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.42,0:14:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,即使我們在想像之舟中\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Even for us, in our Ship of the Imagination,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.19,0:14:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,在時空中所能看到的也是有限的\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}there's a limit to how far we can see in space-time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.83,0:14:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,這是我們的宇宙水平線\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}It's our cosmic horizon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.27,0:14:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,一部分的宇宙處於水平線之下\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Beyond that horizon lie parts of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.37,0:14:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,離我們實在太遙遠了\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}that are too far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.54,0:14:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,在僅有的時間裏\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}There hasn't been enough time
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.54,0:14:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,在宇宙138億年的歷史中\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}in the 13.8 billion year history of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.64,0:14:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,光線還來不及傳遞過來\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}for their light to have reached us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.18,0:15:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,很多人猜測 所有的這一切\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Many of us suspect that all of this...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.62,0:15:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,所有的行星 恆星 星系 星團\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}all the worlds, stars, galaxies and clusters
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.85,0:15:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的可觀測宇宙中的一切\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}in our observable universe...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.29,0:15:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,只是其他宇宙中的滄海一粟\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}is but one tiny bubble in an infinite ocean of other universes...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.67,0:15:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,多重宇宙論\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}...a multiverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.17,0:15:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙之上的宇宙\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Universe upon universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.97,0:15:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有盡頭的世界\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Worlds without end.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.25,0:15:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,感覺很渺小嗎\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Feeling a little small?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.35,0:15:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,相對宇宙來說 我們確實很渺小\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Well, in the contexts of the cosmos, we are small.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.85,0:15:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我們或許只是生活在這浩瀚宇宙中\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}We may just be little guys living on a speck of dust,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.19,0:15:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,漂浮的灰塵粒上的小不點\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}afloat in a staggering immensity,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.59,0:15:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,但我們並不坐井觀天\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}but we don't think small.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.73,0:15:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,現在的宇宙論誕生並不久遠\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}This cosmic perspective is relatively new.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.20,0:15:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,僅僅400年前 我們尚未認識\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}A mere four centuries ago, our tiny world was oblivious
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.50,0:15:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,自身世界以外的宇宙\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}to the rest of the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.50,0:15:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,那時沒有望遠鏡\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}There were no telescopes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.50,0:16:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,只能看到我們肉眼可見的部分\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}The universe was only what you could see with the naked eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.27,0:16:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,在1599年\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Back in 1599,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.38,0:16:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,所有人都認為太陽 行球 星星\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}everyone knew that the Sun, planets and stars
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.75,0:16:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,只是環繞地球的亮光\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}were just lights in the sky that revolved around the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.78,0:16:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,而我們是宇宙的中心\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}and that we were the center of a little universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.85,0:16:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,由上帝為我們創造的宇宙\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}a universe made for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.19,0:16:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,當時全世界只有一個人\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}There was only one man on the whole planet
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.60,0:16:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,想像著一個無盡的浩瀚宇宙\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}who envisioned an infinitely grander cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.46,0:16:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,他是怎麼度過他的1600年除夕？\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}And how was he spending New Year's Eve of the year 1600?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.20,0:16:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,當然是在監獄裏\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Why, in prison, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.16,0:16:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,生命中總有那麼一天\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}There comes a time in our lives
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.36,0:16:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我們發現自己並不是宇宙的中心\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}when we first realize we're not the center of the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.63,0:16:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我們以外還有更廣大的世界\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}that we belong to something much greater than ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.87,0:16:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,這是我們成長所需經歷的一部分\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}It's part of growing up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.87,0:16:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,因為每個人都會經歷到這段過程\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}And as it happens to each of us,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.14,0:16:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的文明也在16世紀\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}so it began to happen to our civilization
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.48,0:16:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,也經歷著這樣的成長\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}in the 16th century.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.18,0:17:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,想像一下望遠鏡問世之前\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Imagine a world before telescopes,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.08,0:17:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,我們只能靠肉眼觀察這個宇宙\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}when the universe was only what you could see with the naked eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.88,0:17:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,很顯然地球是靜止不動的\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}It was obvious that Earth was motionless,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.09,0:17:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,天空中的一切\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}and that everything in the heavens...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.82,0:17:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽 月亮 星星 星球\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}the Sun, the Moon, the stars, the planets...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.16,0:17:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,都圍繞著我們運行  然後\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}revolved around us... and then...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.03,0:17:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,一位名叫哥白尼的波蘭天文學家兼牧師\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}a Polish astronomer and priest named Copernicus
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.33,0:17:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,提出一個地球並非中心的激進假想\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}made a radical proposal. The Earth was not the center.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.33,0:17:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,地球只是和其他星星一樣的行星繞著太陽旋轉\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}It was just one of the planets, and, like them, it revolved around the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.84,0:17:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,很多人 例如宗教改革發起人馬丁·路德\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Many, like the Protestant reformer Martin Luther,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.17,0:17:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,認為這是在對聖經的可恥侮辱\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}took this idea as a scandalous affront to Scripture.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.18,0:17:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,他們震怒了\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}They were horrified.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.45,0:17:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,但是另一個人卻認為哥白尼說的不全面\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}But for one man, Copernicus didn't go far enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.92,0:17:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,他叫焦爾達諾·布魯諾\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}His name was Giordano Bruno and he was a natural-born rebel.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.31,0:17:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,他生性反叛\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}and he was a natural-born rebel.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.48,0:17:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,他渴望打破這狹隘宇宙的枷鎖\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}He longed to bust out of that cramped little universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.68,0:17:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,在那不勒斯做道明會的修道士時\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Even as a young Dominican monk in Naples,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.48,0:17:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,他就與這個世界格格不入\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}he was a misfit.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.94,0:17:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,當時在意大利沒有思想的自由\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}This was a time when there was no freedom of thought in Italy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.69,0:17:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,但是布魯諾渴望瞭解\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}But Bruno hungered to know
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.12,0:17:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,關於上帝創世的一切\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}everything about God's creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.96,0:18:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,他閱讀了被教廷禁止的書籍\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}He dared to read the books banned by the Church,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.37,0:18:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,從此踏上了不歸路\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}and that was his undoing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.49,0:18:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,這些書籍中\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}In one of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.20,0:18:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,有一本的作者是1500年前的古羅馬人\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}an ancient Roman, a man dead for more than 1,500 years
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.20,0:18:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs18\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI}物性論 - 盧克·萊修
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.34,0:18:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,向他描述了一個更廣闊的宇宙\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}whispered to him of a universe far greater,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.31,0:18:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,廣闊的猶如他的上帝一般\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}one as boundless as his idea of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.45,0:18:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,盧克萊修讓他的讀者\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Lucretius asked the reader
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.45,0:18:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,想像站在宇宙的邊緣\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}to imagine standing at the edge of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.86,0:18:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,向外射出一支箭\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}and shooting an arrow outward.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.86,0:18:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,如果箭繼續前進 那麼很明顯\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}If the arrow keeps going, then clearly,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.16,0:18:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙繼續向所謂的邊緣以外延伸\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}the universe extends beyond what you thought was the edge.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.06,0:18:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,但是如果箭不繼續前進\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}But if the arrow doesn't keep going...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.50,0:18:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,比方說 撞在一堵牆上\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}say it hits a wall... then that wall must lie
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.20,0:18:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,那麼牆必然是處在所謂的邊緣之外\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}beyond what you thought was the edge of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.17,0:18:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,那麼如果你站在這堵牆上向外射箭\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Now if you stand on that wall and shoot another arrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.51,0:18:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,也只有這相同的兩個結果\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}there are only the same two possible outcomes...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.24,0:18:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,要麼是飛入無盡的太空\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}it either flies forever out into space,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.65,0:18:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,要麼是撞在某個障礙物上\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}or it hits some boundary
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.65,0:18:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,然後你又可以站在上面射出另一支箭\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}where you can stand and shoot yet another arrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.42,0:18:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,無論如何 宇宙是沒有界限的\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Either way, the universe is unbounded.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.02,0:18:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙必然是無盡的\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}The cosmos must be infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.32,0:19:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,布魯諾深以為然\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}This made perfect sense to Bruno.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.83,0:19:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,他崇拜的上帝是全能的\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}The God he worshiped was infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.19,0:19:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,所以他斷定 上帝創造的宇宙怎會不是無窮\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}So how, he reasoned, could Creation be anything less?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.74,0:19:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,那是他的最後一份穩定工作\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}It was the last steady job he ever had.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.13,0:19:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,後來 當他30歲時\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}And then, when he was 30,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.56,0:19:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,他的一個幻覺從此改變他的一生\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}he had the vision that sealed his fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.23,0:19:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,在這個夢中 他認識到了\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}In this dream, he awakened to a world
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.73,0:19:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,一個包含在一群行星中的世界\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}enclosed inside a confining bowl of stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.80,0:19:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,就是他那個時代的宇宙\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}This was the cosmos of Bruno's time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.26,0:20:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,他感到一陣不舒服的害怕\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}He experienced a sickening moment of fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.83,0:20:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,就像腳下的一切\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}as if the bottom of everything
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.36,0:20:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,正向下墜落\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}was falling away beneath his feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.00,0:20:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,但是他鼓起了勇氣\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}But he summoned up his courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.51,0:20:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我展開自信的翅膀飛向太空\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}I spread confident wings to space
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.35,0:20:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,向上高飛至無盡的天空\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}and soared toward the infinite, leaving far behind me
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.95,0:20:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,將一切的壓力拋在身後\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}what others strained to see from a distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.32,0:20:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,這裏沒有上 沒有下 沒有邊界\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Here, there was no up, no down, no edge,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.72,0:20:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有中心\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}no center.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.29,0:20:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我看見太陽和其他星星一樣\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}I saw that the Sun was just another star,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.73,0:20:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,還有其他被行星伴隨著的恆星\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}and the stars were other Suns, each escorted by other Earths
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.70,0:20:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,就像我們的太陽\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}like our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.33,0:20:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,這巨大的啟示對他就如同墜入愛河\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}The revelation of this immensity was like falling in love.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.54,0:20:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,布魯諾變成了一個傳教士\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Bruno became an evangelist,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.54,0:21:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,他在歐洲各地宣揚他的宇宙無限論\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}spreading the gospel of infinity throughout Europe.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.98,0:21:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,他以為其他上帝的追隨者會同樣接受\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}He assumed that other lovers of God would naturally embrace
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.58,0:21:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,這個對於創世的偉大且榮耀的觀點\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}this grander and more glorious view of Creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.65,0:21:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我是不是太傻了\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}What a fool I was.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.73,0:21:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,在他的祖國 他被羅馬天主教會開除教籍\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}He was excommunicated by the Roman Catholic Church in his homeland,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.36,0:21:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,他不僅被瑞士加爾文長老會驅逐出境\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}expelled by the Calvinists in Switzerland,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.83,0:21:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,還被德國的路德教派驅逐出境\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}and by the Lutherans in Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.07,0:21:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,布魯諾接受了一份邀請到英國牛津大學講課\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Bruno jumped at an invitation to lecture at Oxford, in England.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.34,0:21:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,他認為這是一個機會\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}At last, he thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.21,0:21:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,可以與他類似的人分享他的觀點\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}a chance to share his vision with an audience of his peers.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.95,0:21:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我來介紹一個對於宇宙的嶄新看法\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}I have come to present a new vision of the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.05,0:21:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,哥白尼是對的\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Copernicus was right to argue that our world
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.12,0:21:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的世界並不是宇宙的中心\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}is not the center of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.86,0:21:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,地球繞著太陽旋轉\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}The Earth goes around the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.93,0:21:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,它和其他行星一樣\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}It's a planet, just like the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.43,0:21:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,但哥白尼只是曙光\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}But Copernicus was only the dawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.53,0:21:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,而我為你們帶來日出\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}I bring you the sunrise.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.10,0:22:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,那些星星和我們炙熱的太陽一樣\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}The stars are other fiery suns,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.20,0:22:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,由和地球一樣的天體組成\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}made of the same substance as the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.44,0:22:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,他們也有自己的含水的地球\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}and they have their own watery earths,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.48,0:22:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,上面有著和我們一樣高貴的動物植物\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}with plants and animals no less noble than our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.58,0:22:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,你是瘋了還是太蠢\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Are you mad or merely ignorant?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.88,0:22:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,眾所周知只有一個世界\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Everyone knows there is only one world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.65,0:22:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,那是錯誤的\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}What everyone knows is wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.15,0:22:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我們全能的上帝創造了一個無邊無際的宇宙\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Our infinite God has created a boundless universe
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.16,0:22:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,其中包含了無數的星球\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}with an infinite number of worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.06,0:22:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,你們那的人沒讀過亞里斯多德的書嗎\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Do they not read Aristotle where you come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.09,0:22:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,或者是聖經嗎\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Or even the Bible?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.83,0:22:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,我請求你摒棄老舊和傳統的信仰和權威\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}I beg you, reject antiquity, tradition, faith, and authority.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.47,0:22:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,讓我們重新認識\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Let us begin anew,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.77,0:22:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,質疑我們以為\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}by doubting everything we assume
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.80,0:22:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,-已經被證實的一切 -異端者!\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}- has been proven. - Heretic!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.94,0:22:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,異教徒\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Infidel!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.01,0:22:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,你們信仰的上帝太小了\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Your God is too small.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.45,0:22:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,明智的人本應該從中吸取了教訓\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}A wiser man would have learned his lesson.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.85,0:22:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,可惜布魯諾並不是那個人\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}But Bruno was not such a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.19,0:22:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,他不停的宣揚自己觀點\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}He couldn't keep his soaring vision of the cosmos to himself,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.46,0:22:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,儘管這會帶來沉痛的代價\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}despite the fact that the penalty for doing so
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.43,0:22:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,在他的那個時代 代價是如此的殘酷\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}in his world was the most vicious form
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.46,0:22:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,無情和更嚴厲的懲罰\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}of cruel and unusual punishment.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.07,0:23:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,焦爾達諾·布魯諾生活的那個時代\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Giordano Bruno lived at a time when there was no such thing
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.77,0:23:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有政教分離\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}as the separation of church and state,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.74,0:23:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有言論自由神聖不可侵犯\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}or the notion that freedom of speech was a sacred right of every individual.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.28,0:23:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,表達與傳統信仰相悖的觀點\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Expressing an idea that didn't conform to traditional belief
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.15,0:23:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,會帶來極大的麻煩\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}could land you in deep trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.75,0:23:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,布魯諾不顧一切地回到了意大利\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Recklessly, Bruno returned to Italy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.45,0:23:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,也許是想家了\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Maybe he was homesick.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.12,0:23:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,可是他必須知道\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}But still, he must have known that his homeland
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.39,0:23:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,他的祖國對他來說\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}was one of the most dangerous places in Europe
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.49,0:23:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,是最危險的國家\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}he could possibly go.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.26,0:23:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,由羅馬天主教會管轄的宗教法庭\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}The Roman Catholic Church maintained a system of courts
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.33,0:23:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,被稱為異端裁判所\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}known as the Inquisition,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.17,0:23:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,它唯一職責就是審查和折磨\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}and its sole purpose was to investigate and torment
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.74,0:23:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,與教會持有不同聲音和觀點的人\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}anyone who dared voice views that differed from theirs.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.65,0:23:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,布魯諾很快就被\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}It wasn't long before Bruno fell into the clutches
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.62,0:23:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,思想警察抓獲\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}of the thought police.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.52,0:24:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,這位信奉無限宇宙的流浪者\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}This wanderer, who worshiped an infinite universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.19,0:24:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,在八年的監獄生涯中飽受煎熬\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}languished in confinement for eight years.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.36,0:24:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,儘管受盡殘酷的審訊\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Through relentless interrogations,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.20,0:24:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,他依然不願放棄他的觀點\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}he stubbornly refused to renounce his views.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.93,0:24:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,為什麼教會要花\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Why was the Church willing
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.50,0:24:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,如此長的時間來折磨布魯諾\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}to go to such lengths to torment Bruno?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.21,0:24:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,他們在害怕什麼\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}What were they afraid of?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.62,0:24:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,如果布魯諾是對的 那麼這些聖典\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}If Bruno was right, then the sacred books
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.86,0:24:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,還有教會的權威\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}and the authority of the Church
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.71,0:24:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,都將會受到質疑\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}would be open to question.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.92,0:24:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,最終 異端裁判所的紅衣主教們\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Finally, the cardinals of the Inquisition
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.66,0:24:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,做出了他們的判決\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}rendered their verdict.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.59,0:24:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,你有罪\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}You are found guilty
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.19,0:24:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,你質疑聖父聖子聖靈三位一體\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}of questioning the Holy Trinity
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.06,0:24:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,你質疑耶穌基督的神威\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}and the divinity of Jesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.76,0:24:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,你相信上帝的怒火不會永遠\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Of believing that God's wrath is not eternal,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.07,0:24:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,所有人都會被寬恕\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}that everyone will be saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.57,0:24:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,你斷言其他世界存在的主張\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Of asserting the existence of other worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.51,0:24:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,你寫的所有書\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}All of the books you have written
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.44,0:24:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,都會在聖彼得廣場前焚燬\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}will be gathered up and burned in St. Peter's Square.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.95,0:24:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,尊敬的大人 8年的監禁\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Reverend Father, these eight years of confinement
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.55,0:25:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,給了我很多時間去反省\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}have given me much time to reflect.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.12,0:25:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,然後呢\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}So...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.12,0:25:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,你要放棄你的主張嗎\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}you will recant?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.52,0:25:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,我對造物主的愛和崇敬\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}My love and reverence for the Creator
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.52,0:25:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,激發我對全能的上帝的認識\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}inspires in me the vision of an infinite Creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.20,0:25:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你拒不懺悔的話\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}You shall be turned over to the Governor of Rome
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.80,0:25:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,你會被移交到羅馬總督\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}to administer the appropriate punishment
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.20,0:25:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,予以執行相應的懲罰\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}for those who will not repent.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.37,0:25:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,可能你宣佈這個判決時的恐懼\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}It may be that you are more afraid
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.31,0:25:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,比我聽到判決的時候更厲害\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}to deliver this judgment than I am to hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.78,0:26:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,布魯諾殉難的10年後\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Ten years after Bruno's martyrdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.05,0:26:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,伽利略通過望遠鏡\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Galileo first looked through a telescope,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.52,0:26:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,發現布魯諾的學說確實沒錯\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}realizing that Bruno had been right all along.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.19,0:26:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,銀河系是由肉眼看不到的無數恆星組成\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}The Milky Way was made of countless stars invisible to the naked eye,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.69,0:26:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,天空中的某些光亮其實是其他的行星\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}and some of those lights in the sky were actually other worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.66,0:26:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,布魯諾不是科學家\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Bruno was no scientist.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.97,0:26:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,他只是僥倖猜中了\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}His vision of the cosmos was a lucky guess,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.47,0:26:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,因為沒有證據支持他\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}because he had no evidence to support it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.97,0:27:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,就和其他猜想一樣 也有可能不對\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Like most guesses, it could well have turned out wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.24,0:27:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,但是這個觀點一旦散播出去\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}But once the idea was in the air,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.84,0:27:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,它就給了其他人一個方向\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}it gave others a target to aim at.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.91,0:27:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,哪怕只是為了反駁\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}If only to disprove it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.55,0:27:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,布魯諾大致理解了太空的浩瀚無垠\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Bruno glimpsed the vastness of space.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.25,0:27:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,但他對於時間的驚人無際沒有絲毫概念\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}But he had no inkling of the staggering immensity of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.60,0:27:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,壽命很少超過一個世紀的普通人\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}How can we humans, who rarely live more than a century,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.70,0:27:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,怎麼可能去理解宇宙的歷史\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}hope to grasp the vast expanse of time
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.50,0:27:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,就像浩瀚寬闊的時間長河\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}that is the history of the cosmos?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.74,0:27:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙誕生於138億年前\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}The universe is 13.8 thousand million years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.54,0:27:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,為了更好地想像宇宙的歷史\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}In order to imagine all of cosmic time,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.94,0:27:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,我們把它壓縮成12個月的年歷\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}let's compress it into a single calendar year.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.71,0:27:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,年歷上的1月1號是宇宙誕生的日子\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}The cosmic calendar begins on January 1st with the birth of our universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.73,0:28:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,年歷上包含了從那以後經歷的所有時間\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}It contains everything that's happened since then,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.42,0:28:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,一直到現在\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}up to now,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.80,0:28:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,在這個年歷上的12月31號午夜\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}which on this calendar is midnight December 31st.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.35,0:28:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,按照這個比例 每個月代表10億年\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}On this scale, every month represents about a billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.32,0:28:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,每天代表將就4千萬年\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Every day represents nearly 40 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.88,0:28:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,讓我們盡可能地回到過去\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Let's go back as far as we can,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.77,0:28:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,回到宇宙最開始的時刻\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}to the very first moment of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.86,0:28:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,1月1號 宇宙大爆炸\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}January 1st, the Big Bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.59,0:28:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,目前而言這是我們所能看到最早的時間\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}It's as far back as we can see in time... for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.22,0:28:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,整個宇宙形成於一個比原子還小的點\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Our entire universe emerged from a point smaller than a single atom.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.05,0:28:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,空間在密度極大溫度極高的狀態下爆炸\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Space itself exploded in a cosmic fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.05,0:28:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,由此開始了宇宙的擴張\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}launching the expansion of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.42,0:28:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,並誕生了所有的能量\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}and giving birth to all the energy
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.82,0:28:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,還有已經產生的那些所有我們已知的事物\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}and all the matter we know today.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.79,0:29:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,聽上去很瘋狂\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}I know that sounds crazy,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.12,0:29:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,但是我們有很強力的觀測證據\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}but there's strong observational evidence
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.09,0:29:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,來支持宇宙大爆炸理論\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}to support the Big Bang theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.73,0:29:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,證據還有氦元素在宇宙中的比例\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}And it includes the amount of helium in the cosmos
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.23,0:29:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,以及爆炸殘留的發光無線電頻譜\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}and the glow of radio waves left over from the explosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.90,0:29:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,爆炸後宇宙開始冷卻\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}As it expanded, the universe cooled,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.40,0:29:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,其間有2億年左右的黑暗\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}and there was darkness for about 200 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.31,0:29:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,萬有引力將氣體集聚並且加熱\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Gravity was pulling together clumps of gas and heating them
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.80,0:29:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,直到第一批恆星發出亮光\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}until the first stars burst into light
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.80,0:29:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,相當於1月10號\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}on January 10th.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.94,0:29:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,1月13號 這些恆星開始結合\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}On January 13th, these stars coalesced
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.78,0:29:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,形成第一批小星系\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}into the first small galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.68,0:29:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,這些星系融合成更大的星系\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}These galaxies merged to form still larger ones,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.52,0:29:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,包括我們的銀河系\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}including our own Milky Way,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.89,0:29:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,產生於110億年左右\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}which formed about 11 billion years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.36,0:29:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,就是宇宙年歷上的3月15號\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}on March 15th of the cosmic year.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.07,0:29:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,數千億的恆星中\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Hundreds of billions of suns.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.57,0:29:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,哪個是我們的太陽\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Which one is ours?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.40,0:30:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,此時尚未誕生\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}It's not yet born.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.64,0:30:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,它將從其他恆星的灰燼中產生\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}It will rise from the ashes of other stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.14,0:30:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,看到這些猶如閃光燈般的亮光嗎\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}See those lights flashing like paparazzi?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.38,0:30:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,它們都是超新星\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Each one is a supernova,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.85,0:30:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,一顆超大恆星的耀眼爆炸\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}the blazing death of a giant star.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.02,0:30:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,恆星消亡和誕生的地方\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Stars die and are born in places like this one...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.42,0:30:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,我們稱為星星苗圃\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}a stellar nursery.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.42,0:30:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs18\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI}又稱分子雲
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.32,0:30:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,他們像雨滴般\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}They condense like raindrops
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.03,0:30:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,從巨大的氣態和灰塵雲中凝結\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}from giant clouds of gas and dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.70,0:30:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,他們溫度高的可以把原子中的原子核\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}They get so hot that the nuclei of the atoms
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.70,0:30:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,融合在一起\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}fuse together deep within them
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.23,0:30:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,從而產生了我們呼吸的氧氣 肌肉中的碳元素\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}to make the oxygen we breathe, the carbon in our muscles,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.44,0:30:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,骨頭中的鈣元素 血中的鐵元素\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}the calcium in our bones, the iron in our blood,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.91,0:30:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,所有的這一切都產生於\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}all of it was cooked
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.71,0:30:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,從此消亡的恆星炙熱的內心\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}in the fiery hearts of long-vanished stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.21,0:30:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,你 我 所有人\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}You, me, everyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.95,0:30:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,我們都是由星辰物質組成\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}we are made of star stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.19,0:30:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,星辰物質被不斷循環和濃縮\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}This star stuff is recycled and enriched,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.52,0:30:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,一遍又一遍\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}again and again,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.09,0:30:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,經過幾代恆星的誕生消亡\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}through succeeding generations of stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.03,0:31:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,離我們的太陽誕生還有多久\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}How much longer until the birth of our Sun?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.44,0:31:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,很長時間\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}A long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.24,0:31:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,我們太陽的第一次發光\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}It won't begin to shine
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.54,0:31:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,還要再等60億年\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}for another six billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.08,0:31:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽的生日是8月31號\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Our Sun's birthday is August 31st
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.08,0:31:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,在這個宇宙年歷上\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}on the Cosmic Calendar...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.42,0:31:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,45億年前\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}...four and a half billion years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.72,0:31:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,就像太陽系中其他行星\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}As with the other worlds of our solar system,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.22,0:31:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,地球在一堆氣體和灰塵中產生\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Earth was formed from a disk of gas and dust
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.33,0:31:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,繞著新生的太陽運行\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}orbiting the newborn Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.49,0:31:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,反覆的碰撞產生了一個發光的球狀碎片\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Repeated collisions produced a growing ball of debris.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.34,0:31:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,看到那個小行星了嗎\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}See that asteroid?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.77,0:31:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,不是那個\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}No, not that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.11,0:31:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,那邊的那個\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}The one over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.81,0:31:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的存在歸功於它旁邊的引力\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}We exist because the gravity of that one next to it
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.58,0:31:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,把它輕輕向左推了一英吋\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}just nudged it an inch to the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.75,0:31:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,一英吋有很大的區別嗎\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}What difference could an inch make
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.78,0:31:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,按照太陽系的比例來說\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}on the scale the solar system?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.85,0:31:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,稍等 你馬上就能看到\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Just wait, you'll see.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.32,0:32:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,在最初的10億年裏\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}The Earth took one hell of a beating
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.16,0:32:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,地球飽受摧殘\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}in its first billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.43,0:32:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,任由軌道上的碎片撞擊和融合\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Fragments of orbiting debris collided and coalesced,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.33,0:32:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,直到他們形成了我們的月亮\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}until they snowballed to form our Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.11,0:32:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,月亮是那個暴力紀元的紀念品\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}The Moon is a souvenir of that violent epoch.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.68,0:32:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你站在遠古地球的表面\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}If you stood on the surface of that long ago Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.71,0:32:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,月亮會看上去比現在亮100倍\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}the Moon would have looked a hundred times brighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.45,0:32:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,那時月亮離我們近10倍\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}It was ten times closer back then,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.65,0:32:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,被比現在更強大的引力場吸引著\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}locked in a much more intimate gravitational embrace.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.39,0:32:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,地球冷卻下來 海洋形成了\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}As the Earth cooled, seas began to form.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.36,0:32:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,海浪比現在高1000倍\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}The tides were a thousand times higher then.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.46,0:32:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,經過極漫長的時間 潮汐的摩擦力\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Over the eons, tidal friction within Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.70,0:32:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,將月球推遠\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}pushed the Moon away.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.67,0:32:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,生命差不多在這個時候誕生\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Life began somewhere around here,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.41,0:32:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,9月21號\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}September 21st,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.51,0:32:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,在地球上的35億年前\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}three and a half billion years ago on our little world.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.58,0:32:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我們依然不知道生命如何起源\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}We still don't know how life got started.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.38,0:33:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我們只是知道\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}For all we know,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.05,0:33:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,有可能是來自銀河系的其他地方\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}it may have come from another part of the Milky Way.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.09,0:33:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,生命的起源\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}The origin of life
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.92,0:33:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,是最偉大的未知科學奇跡之一\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}is one of the greatest unsolved mysteries of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.76,0:33:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,生命的演變\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}That's life cooking,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.83,0:33:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,一切生物化學的進化\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}evolving all the biochemical recipes
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.40,0:33:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,充滿了無與倫比的複雜活動\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}for its incredibly complex activities.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.10,0:33:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,到了11月9號 生命開始呼吸 移動\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}By November 9th, life was breathing, moving,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.68,0:33:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,進食和對週遭環境作出反應\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}eating, responding to its environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.58,0:33:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,多虧了這些有開拓性的微生物\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}We owe a lot to those pioneering microbes.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.52,0:33:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,沒錯 就是這些不起眼的傢伙\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Oh, yeah... one other thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.58,0:33:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,他們還發明了繁殖\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}They also invented sex.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.36,0:33:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,12月17號 很特別的一天\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}December 17th was quite a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.56,0:33:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,海洋中生命的發展開始騰飛\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Life in the sea really took off,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.03,0:33:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,形形色色的大型植物和動物\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}it was exploding with a diversity
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.20,0:33:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,爆炸式地發展\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}of larger plants and animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.20,0:33:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,提塔利克魚是最早冒險登陸的動物之一\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Tiktaalik was one of the first animals to venture onto land.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.21,0:33:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,感覺肯定像是造訪另一個星球\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}It must have felt like visiting another planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.08,0:34:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,森林  恐龍\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Forests, dinosaurs,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.48,0:34:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,鳥類 昆蟲\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}birds, insects,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.82,0:34:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,都在12月的最後一周進化而來\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}they all evolved in the final week of December.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.22,0:34:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,第一朵花\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}The first flower...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.09,0:34:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,在12月28號 盛開\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}bloomed on December 28th.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.80,0:34:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,隨著古森林的成長死亡\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}As these ancient forests grew and died
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.57,0:34:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,並被深埋進地下\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}and sank beneath the surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.57,0:34:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,他們的殘骸形成了煤\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}their remains transformed into coal.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.44,0:34:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,3億年後\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}300 million years later,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.07,0:34:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,人類燃燒這些煤來推動文明的發展\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}we humans are burning most of that coal to power
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.41,0:34:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,同時也使我們的文明陷入危機\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}and imperil our civilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.45,0:34:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,還記得那顆在太陽系形成時的\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Remember that asteroid back in the formation
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.85,0:34:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,小行星嗎\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}of the solar system...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.52,0:34:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,那顆被輕輕推動的小行星\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}the one that got nudged a little to the left?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.69,0:34:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,它來了\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Well, here it comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.03,0:34:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙年歷上的12月30號 早晨6點24分\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}It's 6:24 AM on December 30th on the Cosmic Calendar.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.81,0:35:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,在1億年的時間裏\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}For more than a hundred million years,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.77,0:35:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,恐龍曾是這個地球的統治者\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}the dinosaurs were lords of the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.01,0:35:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,當我們的祖先 小型哺乳動物\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}while our ancestors, small mammals,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.78,0:35:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,戰戰兢兢地在地面爬來爬去的時候\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}scurried fearfully underfoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.95,0:35:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,這顆小行星改變了一切\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}The asteroid changed all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.35,0:35:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,假如它沒有被推動\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Suppose it hadn't been nudged at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.19,0:35:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,它會完全和地球擦肩而過\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}It would have missed the Earth entirely,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.02,0:35:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,恐龍恐怕依然存在\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}and for all we know, the dinosaurs might still be here
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.32,0:35:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,但我們不會\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}but we wouldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.96,0:35:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,這是極端突發狀況的好例子\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}This is a good example of the extreme contingency,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.96,0:35:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,生存的偶然性\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}the chance nature, of existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.37,0:35:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙已經誕生超過135億年\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}The universe is already more than 13 and a half billion years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.07,0:35:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,人類仍未出現\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Still no sign of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.91,0:35:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,在這個年歷代表的時間長河中\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}In the vast ocean of time that this calendar represents,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.08,0:35:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,人類在宇宙年歷中的最後一天\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}we humans only evolved within the last hour
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.18,0:35:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,最後一小時進化而來\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}of the last day of the cosmic year.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.56,0:35:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,11點59分46秒\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}11:59 and 46 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.33,0:36:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,全部有記載的歷史發生在最後的14秒裏\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}All of recorded history occupies only the last 14 seconds,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.56,0:36:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,你聽說過的所有人\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}and every person you've ever heard of
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.33,0:36:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,存在於這個點的某個位置\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}lived somewhere in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.20,0:36:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,那些國王 戰役 遷徙 發明\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}All those kings and battles, migrations and inventions,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.18,0:36:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,戰爭和愛情 寫在歷史書中的一切\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}wars and loves, everything in the history books
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.68,0:36:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,都發生在這宇宙年歷中的最後幾秒\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}happened here, in the last seconds of the Cosmic Calendar.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.85,0:36:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,但如果我們想要研究\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}But if we want to explore
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.05,0:36:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙年歷中這段極短的時間\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}such a brief moment of cosmic time...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.22,0:36:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,我們必須改變比例\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}...we'll have to change scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.20,0:36:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我們是這個宇宙的新丁\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}We are newcomers to the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.60,0:36:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的歷史僅僅從宇宙年的最後一晚開始\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Our own story only begins on the last night of the cosmic year.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.04,0:36:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,現在是新年前夜的9點45分\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}It's 9:45 on New Year's Eve.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.44,0:37:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,350萬年前\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Three and a half million years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.88,0:37:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,你我的祖先留下這些足跡\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}our ancestors, yours and mine, left these traces.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.15,0:37:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,我們站了起來和他們區別開來\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}We stood up, and parted ways from them.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.82,0:37:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,自從我們直立行走\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Once we were standing on two feet,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.75,0:37:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的雙眼不在迷戀地面\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}our eyes were no longer fixated on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.92,0:37:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,現在我們可以自由的探索奇跡\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Now we were free to look up in wonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.16,0:37:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,人類存在的大部分時間裏\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}For the longest part of human existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.67,0:37:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,比方說最近的4萬代人\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}say the last 40,000 generations,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.44,0:37:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我們曾是流浪者\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}we were wanderers,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.27,0:37:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,獵人和採集者混住在一起\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}living in small bands of hunters and gatherers,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.47,0:37:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,製作工具 生火\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}making tools, controlling fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.14,0:37:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,給事物起名字\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}naming things,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.15,0:37:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,都發生在宇宙年歷的最後一個小時裏\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}all within the last hour of the Cosmic Calendar.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.62,0:37:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,我們必須改變比例去繼續探尋\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}To find out what happens next, we'll have to change scale
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.13,0:37:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,最後一晚的最後一分鐘\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}to see the last minute of the last night
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.33,0:37:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,發生了什麼\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}of the cosmic year.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.37,0:38:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,11點59分\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}11:59
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.37,0:38:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,以宇宙時間比例來說我們太太太年輕了\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}We're so very young on the time scale of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.04,0:38:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,我們甚至還沒開始畫出第一張畫\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}that we didn't start painting our first pictures
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.67,0:38:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,直到宇宙年歷的最後60秒\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}until the last 60 seconds of the cosmic year,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.28,0:38:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,只不過是3萬年前\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}a mere 30,000 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.02,0:38:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我們發明了天文學\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}This is when we invented astronomy.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.63,0:38:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,事實上我們都是天文學家的後裔\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}In fact, we're all descended from astronomers.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.83,0:38:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的生存要依靠研究星星\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Our survival depended on knowing how to read the stars
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.23,0:38:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,用來預測冬天的到來\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}in order to predict the coming of the winter
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.57,0:38:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,以及獸群的遷徙\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}and the migration of the wild herds.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.20,0:38:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,然後大約1萬年前\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}And then, around 10,000 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.21,0:38:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的生活方式迎來了變革\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}there began a revolution in the way we lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.21,0:38:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的祖先學會了如何改變周圍環境\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Our ancestors learned how to shape their environment,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.48,0:38:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,栽培植物 馴養動物\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}taming wild plants and animals,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.88,0:38:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,耕作土地 定居下來\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}cultivating land and settling down.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.89,0:38:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,這改變了一切\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}This changed everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.49,0:38:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,有史以來第一次\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}For the first time in our history,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.49,0:38:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我們可以擁有超過我們負重能力的東西\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}we had more stuff than we could carry.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.89,0:39:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我們需要把這些數量記錄下來\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}We needed a way to keep track of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.33,0:39:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,午夜前的14秒\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}At 14 seconds to midnight,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.53,0:39:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,大約6千年前 我們發明了書寫\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}or about 6,000 years ago, we invented writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.04,0:39:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,隨後不久我們就開始記錄其他東西\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}And it wasn't long before we started recording
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.54,0:39:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,不僅僅是糧食的數量\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}more than bushels of grain.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.27,0:39:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,書寫讓我們保存我們的想法\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Writing allowed us to save our thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.27,0:39:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,並且跨越時間和空間的傳播它們\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}and send them much further in space and time.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.54,0:39:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,泥板上的細小印記\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Tiny markings on a clay tablet
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.95,0:39:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,成了我們征服有限的生命的手段\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}became a means for us to vanquish mortality.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.22,0:39:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,震撼了整個世界\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}It shook the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.35,0:39:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,摩西出生於7秒之前\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Moses was born seven seconds ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.46,0:39:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,釋迦摩尼 6秒前\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Buddha, six seconds ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.39,0:39:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,耶穌基督 5秒前\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Jesus, five seconds ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.30,0:39:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,穆罕穆德 3秒前\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Mohammed, three seconds ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.73,0:39:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,不到2秒前 不論好壞\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}It was not even two seconds ago that, for better or worse,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.14,0:39:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,地球一邊的人類發現了地球的另一邊\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}the two halves of the Earth discovered each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.47,0:39:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,僅僅在最後的一秒鐘里\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}And it was only in the very last second
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.74,0:39:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,我們開始使用科學\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}of the Cosmic Calendar that we began to use science
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.74,0:39:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,去揭示大自然的秘密和規則\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}to reveal nature's secrets and her laws.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.91,0:39:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,科學方法是如此的強大\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}The scientific method is so powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.65,0:39:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,只用了4個世紀的時間\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}that in a mere four centuries,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.65,0:40:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,就從伽利略第一次看向望遠鏡\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}it has taken us from Galileo's first look through a telescope
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.99,0:40:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,到人類在月球上留下足跡\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}at another world to leaving our footprints on the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.61,0:40:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,它讓我們可以越過時間和空間\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}It allowed us to look out across space and time
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.12,0:40:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,去觀察我們在宇宙時空中的位置\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}to discover where and when we are in the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.89,0:40:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,我們有了瞭解宇宙本質的辦法\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}We are a way for the cosmos to know itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.45,0:40:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,卡爾·薩根30多年前帶領我們進行了首次的宇宙航行\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Carl Sagan guided the maiden voyage of Cosmos a generation ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.55,0:40:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,他不僅是20世紀最成功的\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}He was the most successful science communicator
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.76,0:40:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,科學傳播者\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}of the 20th century,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.26,0:40:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,也是一位首屈一指的科學家\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}but he was first and foremost a scientist.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.03,0:40:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,卡爾為我們瞭解行星\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Carl contributed enormously
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.57,0:40:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,作出了極大的貢獻\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}to our knowledge of the planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.77,0:40:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,他正確地預測了木星的衛星 泰坦 土衛六上\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}He correctly predicted the existence of methane lakes
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.77,0:40:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,有沼氣湖的存在\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}on Saturn's giant moon Titan.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.77,0:40:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,他指出早期地球的大氣層中\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}He showed that the atmosphere of the early Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.08,0:40:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,必然含有強大的溫室氣體\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}must have contained powerful greenhouse gases.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.05,0:40:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,他首先推斷出火星上的季節變化\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}He was the first to understand that seasonal changes on Mars
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.05,0:40:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,是由沙塵暴引起\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}were due to windblown dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.55,0:40:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,卡爾是一位\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Carl was a pioneer
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.12,0:40:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,在探索地球以外智慧生物領域的先驅\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}in the search for extraterrestrial life and intelligence.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.46,0:41:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,太空時代的最初40年裏 每次主要的\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}He played a leading role in every major spacecraft mission
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.76,0:41:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽系探索航天任務 他都擔任了重要的職務\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}to explore the solar system during the first 40 years of the Space Age.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.40,0:41:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,但他做的 不僅僅只有這些\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}But that's not all he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.51,0:41:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,這是卡爾的一本1975年的記事日曆\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}This is Carl Sagan's own calendar from 1975.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.58,0:41:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,我那時在做什麼\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Who was I back then?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.58,0:41:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs18\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI}12月20日 奈爾·德葛拉司·泰森
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.62,0:41:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我只是一個紐約的17歲男孩\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}I was just a 17-year-old kid from the Bronx
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.45,0:41:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,夢想著可以成為科學家\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}with dreams of becoming a scientist,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.85,0:41:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,世界上最著名的天文學家\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}and somehow the world's most famous astronomer found time
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.19,0:41:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,邀請我去紐約州\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}to invite me to Ithaca, in upstate New York,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.03,0:41:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,和他共度一個週六\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}and spend a Saturday with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.83,0:41:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,我記得那天下著雪\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}I remember that snowy day like it was yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.27,0:41:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,他來公車站接我\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}He met me at the bus stop
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.10,0:41:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,帶我參觀了他在康奈爾大學的實驗室\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}and showed me his laboratory at Cornell University.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.00,0:41:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,卡爾從書桌後拿出這本書並在上面為我題字\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Carl reached behind his desk and inscribed this book for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.44,0:41:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs18\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI}《宇宙的聯繫》(The Cosmic Connection)
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.18,0:41:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,"致 尼爾 未來的天文學家\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}"For Neil, a future astronomer.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.88,0:41:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,卡爾"\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Carl."
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.72,0:42:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,結束後 他開車送我去公車站\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}At the end of the day, he drove me back to the bus station.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.15,0:42:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,雪下得更大了\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}The snow was falling harder.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.15,0:42:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,他寫下他的電話號碼 家裏的電話\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}He wrote his phone number... his home phone number...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.16,0:42:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,寫在一張小紙片上 然後跟我說 "如果公車沒有來\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}on a scrap of paper and he said, "If the bus can't get through,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.66,0:42:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,打電話給我 就在我家過夜"\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}call me and spend the night at my home with my family."
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.50,0:42:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我當時已經決定要當一名科學家\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}I already knew I wanted to become a scientist,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.33,0:42:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,但是那天下午 我認識到\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}but that afternoon, I learned from Carl
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.74,0:42:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,我要做他那樣的人\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}the kind of person I wanted to become.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.00,0:42:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,他幫助了我 還有其他很多人\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}He reached out to me and to countless others,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.68,0:42:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,激勵我們去學習 教授 研究科學\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}inspiring so many of us to study, teach and do science.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.18,0:42:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,科學研究是一份需要合作的事業\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Science is a cooperative enterprise,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.58,0:42:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,持續幾代人的時間\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}spanning the generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.98,0:42:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,就如同一支火炬在老師與學生的手中傳遞\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}It's the passing of a torch from teacher to student to teacher,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.32,0:42:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,一群偉大的思想從遠古貫穿\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}a community of minds reaching back to antiquity
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.83,0:42:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,直至未來的星空\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}and forward to the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.83,0:42:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,現在跟我來\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Now, come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.66,0:42:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的旅程才剛剛開始\N{\fs14\fn微软雅黑}Our journey is just beginning.
